   "source": [
    "# `pseudo_gravity_packing`\n",
    "This is a form of random sequential addition (`rsa`) that mimics gravity by always putting the next sphere at the lowest possible location."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "f6b2c2e0",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:35.388043Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:35.387723Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:37.568822Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:37.568273Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import porespy as ps\n",
    "ps.visualization.set_mpl_style()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "724e738b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `im`\n",
    "The image into which the spheres should be inserted.  Spheres will be inserted into the ``True`` locations, as if these  indicate void space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "6c3e5994",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:37.571914Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:37.571718Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:39.204464Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2022-04-25T01:54:39.203929Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 383,
       "width": 670
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "im = ps.generators.cylindrical_plug(shape=[151, 101, 101], axis=0)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=~im, r=8, maxiter=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[8, 4])\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(packing[40, ...], interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing[..., 50], interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "24dcbcaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `r`\n",
    "The radius of the spheres to add:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "3c438335",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:39.209064Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2022-04-25T01:54:39.208875Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2022-04-25T01:54:40.134786Z",

    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 583,
       "width": 861
      }
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 6])\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 5\n",
    "im = ps.generators.cylindrical_plug(shape=[151, 101, 101], axis=0)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=~im, r=r, maxiter=500)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(ps.visualization.xray(~packing, axis=2).T, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "\n",
    "r = 10\n",
    "im = ps.generators.cylindrical_plug(shape=[151, 101, 101], axis=0)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=~im, r=r, maxiter=100)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(ps.visualization.xray(~packing, axis=2).T, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },

   "id": "91b52777",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `clearance`\n",
    "The spheres can be forced to have some spacing between them by setting ``clearance > 0``, or they can overlap if ``clearance < 0``:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "c55915a8",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2022-04-25T01:54:40.138313Z",

   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 5])\n",
    "\n",
    "im = np.zeros([300, 300], dtype=bool)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=im, r=r, clearance=3, maxiter=500)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "\n",
    "im = np.zeros([300, 300], dtype=bool)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=im, r=r, clearance=-1, maxiter=100)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "264f17f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## `protrusion`\n",
    "\n",
    "The spheres can be allowed to protrude into the foreground, or displaced away from the foreground by using a positive or negative value, respectively:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "id": "183766dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]

       "width": 1011
      }

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=[12, 5])\n",
    "\n",
    "im = ps.generators.blobs([300, 300], porosity=0.2, seed=0)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=im, r=r, protrusion=3)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(packing + im*2.0, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[0].axis(False)\n",
    "\n",
    "im = ps.generators.blobs([300, 300], porosity=0.1, seed=0)\n",
    "packing = ps.generators.pseudo_gravity_packing(im=im, r=r, protrusion=-5, maxiter=100)\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(packing + im*2.0, interpolation='none', origin='lower')\n",
    "ax[1].axis(False);"
   ]
  },
  {

   "id": "7016973c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "Controls the direction of gravity.  The default is 0, which means the spheres fall towards the x=0 axis."
